article.description: Mikel Beyers had 20 points as Marshall narrowly beat UTSA 82-77 on Saturday.
article.headline: Beyers scores 20 to lead Marshall over UTSA 82-77
article.linkText: Beyers scores 20 to lead Marshall over UTSA 82-77
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Mikel Beyers had 20 points as Marshall narrowly beat UTSA 82-77 on Saturday. Jarrod West had 15 points and seven assists for Marshall (16-15, 10-8 Conference USA). Andrew Taylor added 12 points. Taevion Kinsey had 10 points and six rebounds. Marshall totaled 52 first-half points, a season high for the team. Jhivvan Jackson had 37 points and 11 rebounds for the Roadrunners (13-18, 7-11). Keaton Wallace added 13 points. Jacob Germany had 10 points. The Thundering Herd leveled the season series against the Roadrunners with the win. UTSA defeated Marshall 72-63 on Feb. 13. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
